news.title: Visakhapatnam civic body to clear 170 pending building plan applications soon
news.para: The commissioner added that they will utilise the ward secretariat system to approach and alert the applicants over the shortfalls in their applications.

news.title: Ahmedabad: AFES issues notices to 350 buildings on fire NOCs
news.para: These buildings include hospitals, clinics, schools, and commercial and residential schemes. The managements of these buildings must renew their fire NOCs a month before these expire.

news.title: Over one lakh illegal buildings in Hyderabad sit on tinderbox
news.para: Barely anything has been done to tackle the issue of illegal constructions across the city. In Hyderabad, there are over a lakh such buildings, many of which are unsafe owing to a lack of setbacks and illegal construction of extra floors, and located in dense neighbourhoods.

news.title: Defaulters to pay for razing of illegal structures in Thane
news.para: Commissioner Abhijit Bangar has laid down a protocol for the civic staff wherein the cost will now be recovered either directly from the owners or will be marked as default in tax and set the process for attachment of the owner’s property after following the mandated process.

news.title: Himachal Pradesh: Deadlock remains over cement freight charges as plants, truckers meet fail
news.para: ​The representatives of the truck unions said that no decision has been reached and they are waiting for the report of Himachal Consultancy Organisation (HIMCON) following which the rates would be notified by the government.

news.title: MHADA projects to now offer swimming pool, gym
news.para: Mhada has constructed 2,683 flats spread over 21 buildings, each 23 storey high, for the Economically Weaker Sections (EWS) and Low Income Group at this prime location.

news.title: Kochi: Auction of Holy Faith assets gets just 11 bids, deferred
news.para: ​The highest amount quoted in the bid request was only Rs 46.50 lakh against the expected value of crores of rupees since the properties to be auctioned are situated in prime locations.

news.title: Haryana RERA restrains Mahira Group from cancelling allotment over dues
news.para: The developer, the allottees alleged, had threatened to cancel the allotment of units for non-payment of a monetary demand raised by the Group in the first week of January.

news.title: KKR blocks REIT withdrawals in latest redemption wave
news.para: KKR told investors of its KKR Real Estate Select Trust Inc this week that it received redemption requests greater than 5% of its quarterly net asset value as of the end of December.

news.title: PM launches title deed distribution for over 52,000 nomadic families in north Karnataka
news.para: ​This Hakku Patra will secure future of thousands of people living in the "Thandas" (Lambani habitats) in Kalaburagi, Bidar, Yadgiri, Raichur and Vijayapura districts, he noted.

news.title: HIL appoints Akshat Seth as its new MD and CEO
news.para: The move comes after Dhirup Roy Choudhary resigned as the current MD & CEO of HIL with effect from January 31, 2023.

news.title: Now, consent of only 51% members required for redevelopment of buildings in Navi Mumbai
news.para: "The CIDCO has included a provision that the building can be reconstructed with the consent of only 51 per cent of the members of the housing society instead of the earlier 100 per cent," the town planning authority in Navi Mumbai said.

news.title: Illegal houses on comunidade, government land will be razed: Goa CM
news.para: The state on Wednesday passed the Goa Regularisation of Unauthorised Construction (Amendment) Bill, 2023. Revenue minister Atanasio ‘Babush’ Monserrate said at least 4,800 applications are pending.

news.title: Three times water tariff for builders who construct without PWD nod in Goa
news.para: There is an issue of water not reaching to some of the complexes because the builders did not come to the PWD to check if the department can provide water supply to the complexes, Cabral said during a calling attention motion.

news.title: Truck operators protest against closure of cement plants in Himachal Pradesh
news.para: The two cement plants at Barmana (ACC) and Darlaghat (Ambuja Cements) are closed for the past 35 days, following a dispute over freight charges and operators engaged in carriage of cement and clinkers are on roads.
